{
  "texts": [
    "Each sub-problem is then tackled by a symbolic regression method of choice.",
    "The authors created the Feynman SR database (see Sect. 8) to test their approach.",
    "All the basic equations and 90% of the bonus equations were solved by their algorithm, outperforming Eureqa.",
    "Deep symbolic regression (DSR) (Petersen 2019) is an RL-based search method for symbolic regression that uses a generative recurrent neural network (RNN).",
    "RNN defines a probability distribution (p) over mathematical expressions , and batches of expres- sions T = { (i) } N i=1 are stochastically generated."
  ]
}